condition.narrative: Borrower to take a decision on (i) treatment of existing stock of NHA debt, (ii) mode of all future NHA funding provided thruannual PSDP; and carry out a review of available options for financing.
Except as the Association shall otherwise agree, the Borrower shall ensure that, during Project imp, NHA will: (a) carry out itsinvestment and maintenance program in compliance with the MTBF.
NHA review with IDA, the report referred to in Sec 2.7 (b) and take all measures required to ensure the efficient complet ion ofthe Project and the achievement of the objectives thereof.
NHA shall (a) maintain and operate RMA in accordance with the relevant rules, regulations & standard operating procedures notifiedfrom time to time in consultation with the Association and the Bank.
NHA shall ensure that no works will be undertaken under the second and subsequent phases of Part A of the Project unless relevantEMPs & RAPs approved by IDA/Bank have been prepared.
NHA shall prepare, under TOR satisfactory to IDA/Bank, and furnish to IDA/Bank a report integrating the results of the mo nitoring&evaluation activities pursuant to Sec 2.7(a).
NHA shall, throughout the period of Project implementation, prepare quarterly progress reports, in form & substance s atisfactoryto IDA/Bank, on the imp. of EMPs, RPF and RAPs.
The Borrower shall make the proceeds of the Credit available to NHA as a capital contribution on a non-reimbursable basis, inaccordance with the Borrower's standard budgetary procedures.
